title.narrative: MONITORING AND EVALUATION

description.narrative: By 2016, data collection and management systems provide sex and age disaggregated data on women and children for national planning and timely reporting on MDGs, CRC and Vision 2030 at national and sub-national levels., which contributes to Building Capacity For Evaluation, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Unicef Capacity For Programming On Gender. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By December 2016, evidence-based communication and advocacy for chidlren's rights and mechanisms to monitor child-related systems and national priorities strengthened.

description.narrative: During this programme cycle UNICEF has increased access to disaggregated data on women and children through development of an online monitoring dashboard for the national development plan Vision 2030, finalization and dissemination of a Multiple Indicator Cluster Survey (MICS); in addition to research activities focussing on vulnerable populations. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:13/12/2016

title.narrative: % of government ministries departments or agencies (MDAs)utilizing on-line monitoring framework for reporting on Vision 2030

target.value: 2016:50% of government ministries departments or agencies (MDAs)utilizing on-line monitoring framework for reporting on Vision 2030 by 2014

actual.value: 2016:Oversight team has estimated that the system costs for decentralization of reporting will not be cost effective for 48 indicators. Ministries, Departments and Agencies submit reports via email. Indicator will be discontinued 31.12.2015.

title.narrative: Output from DevInfo database on child protection utilized in production of government reports

target.value: 2016:Output from databases utilized in production of Vision 2030 reports by June 2014

actual.value: 2016:CP database partially updated on an annual basis, updates challenged by HR shifts in some agencies. Ad hoc publications continue to recognize and use JamStats database as an institutional dataset.

title.narrative: Key indicators on women and children updated and available by relevant age-groups, geographical region and sex

baseline.value: MICS 4 survey conducted - report to be published in 2012

target.value: 2016:MICS 5 implemented and report produced and disseminated by 2016

actual.value: 2016:MICS 5 implementation delayed to pursue a more comprehensive approach to addressing Jamaica's data gaps with the Government of Jamaica and identify funding.

title.narrative: Existence of on-line monitoring framework for Vision 2030 Jamaica

actual.value: 2016:On-line monitoring dashboard for Vision 2030 – Jamaica established and launched in December 2013. Target met Improvements to dashboard were launched and went live in December 2015
